==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cockhorse
<hw>Cock"horse`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A
child's rocking-horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ride a <qex>cockhorse</qex> to Banbury cross.</q> <rj><qau>Mother
Goose.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A high or tall horse.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cockhorse</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Cockhorse
<hw>Cock"horse`</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Lifted up, as one
is on a tall horse.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lofty in feeling; exultant; proud;
upstart.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our painted fools and <qex>cockhorse</qex> peasantry.</q>
<rj><qau>Marlowe.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cockieleekie</ent>⟦br⟧
